@startuml
title Math Primitives - Class View

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

namespace spk {
	class Vector2<T> {
		+ x : T
		+ y : T
	}

	class Vector3<T>
	class Vector4<T>

	class Rect2D {
		+ position : Vector2
		+ size : Vector2
		+ contains(point)
		+ intersection(rect)
	}

	class Matrix
	class Quaternion
	class ApproxValue<T>
	class Constants
	class Math
}

spk.Rect2D *-- spk.Vector2
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector2
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector3
spk.Matrix ..> spk.Vector4
spk.Quaternion ..> spk.Vector3
spk.Math ..> spk.Constants
spk.Math ..> spk.ApproxValue

note bottom
Math primitives are value types. Higher-level systems depend
on them, but they avoid owning application or rendering state.
end note

@enduml
